This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development of a multilingual topic model for unaligned text. It also involves the use of stochastic EM to discover multilingual latent topics, which is a common technique used in natural language processing. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as topic modeling is a popular machine learning technique. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as topic modeling is often used in information retrieval tasks such as document clustering and classification. 

It may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as topic modeling is a subfield of AI and this paper involves the development of a probabilistic model. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper deals with analyzing corpora composed of documents in two languages, which could include multimedia content such as videos or images.
